<br>
I will max Str, Con, Dex and Cha.<br>
I have BS at 50+ with current equipment and realm rank.<br>
<br>
But... given my current budget and drop situation, I have to decide which is more important for me, so could someone please bring the following list to a reasonable order ?<br>
<br>
Qui<br>
Hitpoints<br>
Skills (Sword, Parry) <br>
Resists (which ones ??)<br>
<br>
Thanks a lot ! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kluk@teamskald>Kluk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/13/03 4:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=604.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re :</span><hr size=1> Resists is top priority. <br>
- Slash, Crush and Thrust (especially for a chain tank)<br>
You should also try to max out every magical resist, but if you need to focus only on 2-3 I suggest Body, spirit,  and cold (Have a look  <a href="http://daoc.gamescape.com/handler.cfm?app=resources/gameplay&method=MagicResistances" target="_new">here</a> ti make up your mind.<br>
<br>
With the end game quests rewards it's not that difficult to max out everything needed. Here's my actual template : <a href="http://library.l9c.org/profile.php?cId=85#Details" target="_new">here</a> <br>
Boots, legs, helm and axe are spellcrafted(99%) to get STR/CHA/CON/Hp/Axe/Slash and Energy near cap (Next I'll change the hauberk cause it's 30% bonus only and has no reverse proc) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 301<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/13/03 9:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=604.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm</span><hr size=1> Why max dex if you have limited resources ? (at the very least, you'll probably get more defensive bang for the buck by maxing parry)<br>
<br>
